# 🏠 Smart House Price Prediction System

This project is a Machine Learning-based application that predicts house prices using various features and provides a comparison between actual predicted price and broker-influenced pricing.

## 🚀 Features
- Predict house prices using Linear Regression
- Simplified user input (rooms & house type)
- Comparison of:
  - Actual Price
  - Broker Price (inflated estimate)
  - Adjusted Price (based on surroundings)
- Data visualization using graphs

## 🧠 Machine Learning Approach
- Algorithm: Linear Regression
- Dataset: - Model trained using structured housing data features
- Features include rooms, location factors, and environmental indicators
- Linear Regression used for price prediction
- Data preprocessing and feature selection performed
- Model trained and evaluated using test data
- Designed a simplified real-world pricing system incorporating broker influence and environmental adjustments
## 📊 Visualization
- Scatter plot for Actual vs Predicted prices
- Bar chart for price comparison

## 🛠️ Technologies Used
- Python
- Pandas
- Scikit-learn (Linear Regression)
- Matplotlib (visualization)
- Streamlit (web interface)

## 🎯 Use Case
Helps users estimate fair housing prices and understand how brokers may influence pricing.

## 📌 Future Improvements
- Location-based predictions
- Real-time data integration
- Advanced ML models
